headline.main: INDIANS FIGHT WAY FROM LIBYAN TRAP; Two Columns of Bengazi's Defenders Battle Nazis and Rejoin the British R.A.F. RAINS NEW BLOWS Blasts at Rommel's Supply Line -- Torpedo Planes Set Fire to Laden Tanker

lead_paragraph: CAIRO, Egypt, Jan. 31 -- After having fought their way through German positions, two columns of the Seventh Indian Brigade have reached the British main forces outside the Bengazi area, thus foiling, at least partially, the German plan to trap the defenders of Bengazi between columns that cut off the city from north, east and south.
abstract: 2 Indian columns fight way from Axis trap to rejoin Brit, Bengazi area
